HEADWORD: Pholas
<hw>Pho"las</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pholades</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>fwla`s</grk>, <grk>fwla`dos</grk>, a kind of mollusk.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of marine bivalve
mollusks of the genus <gen>Pholas</gen>, or family
<fam>Pholadid⟦ae⟧</fam>. They bore holes for themselves in clay, peat,
and soft rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pholistoma</ent>⟦br⟧
